# TinyCare Parse Server

Parse Server backend for TinyCare mobile application with MongoDB Atlas integration.

## 🚀 Features

- Parse Server API
- Parse Dashboard (Web UI)
- MongoDB Atlas integration
- RESTful API endpoints
- Authentication & Authorization
- Real-time queries

## 📋 Prerequisites

- Node.js 16+ 
- pnpm
- MongoDB Atlas account

## 🛠️ Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd TNC-server-service

# Install dependencies
pnpm install

# Create environment file
cp .env.example .env
```

## 🔧 Environment Variables

Create `.env` file with the following variables:

```env
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/database
APP_ID=your-app-id
MASTER_KEY=your-master-key
SERVER_URL=your-server-url
DASHBOARD_USER=admin
DASHBOARD_PASS=your-secure-password
COOKIE_SECRET=your-random-secret-key
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=production
```

## 🔐 Generate Secure Passwords

```bash
# Generate secure passwords for production
pnpm run generate-passwords

# Check production setup
pnpm run check-production
```

## 🏃‍♂️ Running the Application

### Development
```bash
# Run Parse Server only
pnpm dev

# Run Parse Server + Dashboard
pnpm run start-all

# Run Dashboard only
pnpm run dashboard
```

### Production
```bash
pnpm start
```

## 📊 Parse Dashboard

Access the web dashboard at: `http://localhost:4040`
- Username: `admin`
- Password: `admin123`

## 🔗 API Endpoints

- **Base URL**: `http://localhost:5000/parse`
- **Health Check**: `GET /parse/health`
- **Server Info**: `GET /parse/serverInfo`
- **Objects**: `GET/POST/PUT/DELETE /parse/classes/{className}`

### Required Headers
```javascript
{
  'X-Parse-Application-Id': 'your-app-id',
  'X-Parse-Master-Key': 'your-master-key', // For admin operations
  'Content-Type': 'application/json'
}
```

## 📱 Client SDK Integration

```javascript
// Initialize Parse SDK
Parse.initialize("your-app-id");
Parse.serverURL = "https://your-app.onrender.com/parse";
```

## 🚀 Deployment

This app is configured for deployment on Render.com with automatic MongoDB Atlas connection.

## 📝 Scripts

- `pnpm start` - Production server
- `pnpm dev` - Development with nodemon
- `pnpm run dashboard` - Parse Dashboard
- `pnpm run start-all` - Server + Dashboard
- `pnpm test` - Test MongoDB connection

## 🛡️ Security

- Environment variables for sensitive data
- Master Key protection
- CORS enabled
- Express security middleware

